Background

		Mr. Alexander E. Perriello, III, also known as Alex, serves as the President of Realogy Global Services LLC and CGRN, Inc. Mr. Perriello served as the Chief Executive Officer of Realogy Franchise Group LLC (formerly, Cendant Real Estate Franchise Group) since April 2004 until March 31, 2017. He served as the President of Realogy Franchise Group LLC from April 2004 to October 13, 2016. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Coldwell Banker Real Estate ... Corporation from 1997 to 2004. He began his career as a Sales Associate, has worked in almost every facet of the real estate business. He shares the entrepreneurial spirit of his affiliates as a one-time independent real estate broker and owner of a chain of retail stores. After joining Coldwell Banker in 1983, Mr. Perriello held management positions in product development, real estate services, marketing and operations. He played an integral role in the restructuring and development of Coldwell Banker following its 1996 acquisition by Cendant (then HFS) and its relocation to Parsippany, N.J. Mr. Perriello is widely recognized as a real estate industry leader and keen observer in the areas of policy and market trends. With more than 25 years in the real estate industry, he has long been among its distinguished leaders and is a frequent speaker at industry events. He Chairman Emeritus of Realogy Franchise Group at Realogy Holdings Corp., since April 7, 2017. He has been Chairman Emeritus of Realogy Franchise Group LLC since March 31, 2017. He served as the Chairman of Realogy Franchise Group LLC (formerly, Cendant Real Estate Franchise Group) since April 2004 until March 31, 2017. He serves as a Director of WREM, Inc. and CGRN, Inc. He has also appeared as an industry expert on various news programs, including CNN, CNBC and FOX News. During this time, he was acclaimed by REALTOR Magazine as "The Great Innovator" and one of its "25 Most Influential People in Real Estate." In addition, Mr. Perriello is widely quoted in real estate trade magazines as well as business and consumer publications, including USA Today, Fortune, Money and The Wall Street Journal.Read Full Background




